---
import StaticLayout from '@layouts/StaticLayout.astro';
---

<StaticLayout title="More Information">
  <div class="pb-12 px-6 space-y-10 uppercase md:grid grid-cols-2 justify-items-center items-center md:h-full gap-10">
    <header class="justify-self-start max-md:fixed max-md:bg-white pt-12 z-20 w-11/12">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-pink text-7xl md:text-8xl lg:text-9xl text-center tracking-tighter pt-6 md:text-start">More Info</h1>
    </header>
    <main class="space-y-5 max-w-md max-md:pt-44">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-pink text-4xl tracking-tighter">
          Where
        </h1>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base underline-offset-2">
          Our wedding reception is at the fabulous Hoxton hotel in Southwark. We’re up on the 12<sup class="lowercase">th</sup> floor, and our entrance and lifts are on the far righthand side of the building. (Just ask the main reception if you’re not sure!)
        </p>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base underline-offset-2">
          Address - 40 Blackfriars Rd, South Bank, London SE1 8NY
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-pink text-4xl tracking-tighter">
          Accommodation
        </h1>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base">
          Book a room at the <a href="https://thehoxton.com/london/southwark/" target="_blank" class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base underline underline-offset-2">The Hoxton</a> 
          for the wedding. Make sure to pick Southwark location and use the discount
          code HITCHED0224 for 15% off!
        </p>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base">
          Or stay at the nearby Novotel or Ibis hotels.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-pink text-4xl tracking-tighter">
          Getting Around
        </h1>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base">
          The closest train stations are Waterloo and London Bridge stations – both about a 10 min walk.
        </p>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base">
          Southwark Tube (Jubilee Line) is the closest underground station.
        </p>
        <p class="text-black uppercase text-sm md:text-base [&_a]:underline underline-offset-2">
          Download <a href="https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/citymapper-live-transport/id469463298" target="_blank">City Mapper</a> for making your way around the city. It has real-time transport info and route planning.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>
</StaticLayout>
